      },
      "pages": [
        {
          "id": "rules.md",
          "title": "Coworld MTG rules",
          "content": {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Coworld MTG is a two-player Magic duel with balanced mirrored matches and a color-swapping Red Rush versus Green Stompy series. The pinned Phase engine is authoritative for draws, mana, casting, timing, targets, priority, the stack, combat, triggers, state-based actions, and game outcomes. Players may submit only exact actions offered by Phase for their private view. Hidden hands and libraries remain redacted from opponents and spectators. Multi-game matches alternate seats, and color-swap variants also exchange decks between players after each game. Clocks and explicit concessions are enforced by the host."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  },
